Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:07.100 --> 00:00:14.100
Hi Friends,
Are you getting the error code 0x8024402C

00:00:15.040 --> 00:00:21.119
on installing updates via Windows update in
your Windows 8 PC? Let's go ahead and see

00:00:21.119 --> 00:00:23.790
how you can resolve the issue.

00:00:23.790 --> 00:00:28.660
On the Start screen, click on the "Internet
Explorer" tile to open it.

00:00:28.660 --> 00:00:35.559
Click on the Gear icon, and then click on
Internet Options

00:00:35.559 --> 00:00:41.890
On the Connections tab, click on LAN Settings,
and then click on the Advanced option.

00:00:41.890 --> 00:00:48.229
If there is any entry in the Exceptions section
delete it, and then click OK.

00:00:48.229 --> 00:00:54.229
Click "Yes" to turn off the proxy connection
Click "OK" twice, and then minimize the

00:00:54.229 --> 00:00:58.699
Internet Explorer
Go to the start screen

00:00:58.699 --> 00:01:03.309
Right click on any blank area, and then click
on All Apps

00:01:03.309 --> 00:01:10.309
Under Windows System, right click on the Command
prompt, and then click on Run as Administrator.

00:01:11.200 --> 00:01:22.000
On the command Prompt window
Type "netsh [space] winhttp [space] reset

00:01:22.119 --> 00:01:32.900
[space] proxy", and press ENTER key
Type "net [space] stop [space] wuauserv",

00:01:32.900 --> 00:01:42.300
and press ENTER key
Type "net [space] start [space] wuauserv"

00:01:42.369 --> 00:01:47.759
, and press ENTER key
Type "exit", and press ENTER key

00:01:47.759 --> 00:01:53.880
Now you can try to install the updates,
To do so move the mouse pointer to the top

00:01:53.880 --> 00:02:00.210
right corner of the screen to access the Charms
menu, and then click on the Settings charm

00:02:00.210 --> 00:02:07.210
Click on Change PC settings
Under PC Settings, select Windows Update

00:02:07.490 --> 00:02:11.850
Click on Check for updates now to check for
updates

00:02:11.850 --> 00:02:17.140
If it works then it's fine
If not close the Windows Update window

00:02:17.140 --> 00:02:22.030
Go to Desktop and launch Internet Explorer
again

00:02:22.030 --> 00:02:29.030
On the Tools menu, click on Internet Options
Click on the Connections tab, and then click

00:02:29.140 --> 00:02:34.110
on LAN Settings,
Select the checkbox next to Automatically

00:02:34.110 --> 00:02:38.500
Detect Settings, and then click OK twice.

00:02:38.500 --> 00:02:46.640
Close Internet explorer, and then try to install the Windows update again.

00:02:46.640 --> 00:02:51.610
Wasn't that quick and easy? Thanks for watching!

